Abby Wambach: USA's leading scorer calls for more women in Fifa
Media playback is not supported on this deviceThe USA's all-time leading international goalscorer Abby Wambach says "there needs to be more women in Fifa".The2012 women's world player of the yearsays she would be "open to having conversations" about performing a role for football's governing body, but first wants to focus on the upcoming World Cup in Canada.Wambach has won two Olympic gold medals and has scored a record 178 goals in 236 international matches.She was speaking to BBC Sport on International Women's Day.